
                               SPERIS LEGACY

    THE PLOT

    It was the same old story, the evil Prince  Gallus  slew  his  brother
    Kale  to gain the Kingdom. Now only Cho, boyhood friend of Kale, stood
    in his way. This was Cho`s chance for adventure. His chance  to  prove
    his  worth.  He  couldn`t  wait for Gallus to seek him out. Instead he
    would take the fight to Gallus, and end the threat to  the  Sperisland
    forever.

    THE LAND OF SPERIS

    Cho  begins  his  quest from within his home in Sharma City. The quest
    through Speris will take you through many adventures in different  and
    unusual  locations.  You play the character Cho, guide him through his
    quest to overcome the evil Gallus. You are given complete  freedom  to
    traverse the entire land of Speris. All locations are there for you to
    discover and explore, be wary as some are hidden  and  not  so  easily
    found..!

    On  your  journey  you will meet many weird and wonderful people, both
    good and evil, who may hinder or help your quest.

    LOADING THE GAME

    Machine Requirements

    The Speris Legacy will  run  on  any  1200,  4000  or  CD32  and  most
    compatible CD-ROM drives. Disk Version

    Reset  your  Amiga and insert disk 1, the game will then automatically
    load. Follow all onscreen prompts and change disks only when requested
    to  do so. Remember to keep game disks write-protected at all times to
    prevent accidental erasure of game  data.  A  hard  disk  installation
    program is available, please refer to the readme file.

    THE GAME SCREENS

    1. Title screen
    This screen is presented on loading. All options are selected  by  use
    of cursor keys, joypad or joystick to highlight the desired option and
    pressing the primary fire button or key.

    START NEW GAME - Cho begins his quest.
    LOAD GAME - See LOAD/SAVE GAME section to use this option.
    OPTIONS MENU - This allows access to a sub-screen where you can select
    your Control Method, Redefine Keys or return to the Main Menu.
    Control Method allows selection of keyboard; one button joystick; two
    button joypad or CD32 joypad.
    Key definitions allows you to completely redefine all the keyboard
    functions in the game.

    2. Main Screen

    SELECTED OBJECT - TOP LEFT OF SCREEN(2ND ICON) - Shows  which  of  the
    items Cho has selected for use.

    SELECTED  WEAPON  - TOP LEFT OF SCREEN (1ST ICON) - Shows which of thr
    weapons Cho has selected for use.

    SCORE - TOP MIDDLE OF SCREEN - Extra  points  are  gained  by  killing
    enemies and solving puzzles.

    VITALITY  BAR  -  TOP RIGHT OF SCREEN (VIT) - Cho`s health. If this is
    depleted Cho will perish and his quest has ended.

    EXPERIENCE BAR - TOP RIGHT OF SCREEN (EXP) - Gives a measure of  Cho`s
    progress.  As  you  gather experience by overcoming monsters and other
    evil inhabitants. You are rewarded with an increase in vitality.

    POWER BAR - BOTTOM MIDDLE OF SCREEN - Using  this  will  increase  the
    efectiveness of certain weapons.

    GEMS - BOTTOM LEFT OF SCREEN (3 FIGURE ICON) - Shows how many gems you
    carry. Gems are the main form of currency within the Sperislands.  Cho
    can use those which he collects to buy items in the shops.

    BOMBS  - FAR BOTTOM LEFT - Shows how many bombs you carry. Cho can use
    bombs to remove certain obsticles in his path. A more adept player can
    use bombs to a more deadly effect.

    3. INVENTORY SCREEN

    WEAPONS - LEFT - All of the weapons Cho has discovered in his quest
    are displayed here.

    OTHER OBJECTS - RIGHT - All non-weapon items discovered by Cho are
    displayed here.

    4. THE MAP SCREEN

    The map screen  is  automatically  displayed  whenever  Cho  leaves  a
    location.  To  move from one location to another simply move Cho along
    the map to the place you wish  to  visit.  When  a  question  mark  is
    displayed  above  Cho`s  head  press the primary fire button or key. A
    prompt will be displayed giving you the option  to  confirm  that  you
    wish to enter a location.

    5. LOAD/SAVE GAME

    Cho`s  progress  can  be saved at any point within the game. Accessing
    the save game screen can be acheived by pressing F5 on the keyboard.

    ----------------------------
    |                          |
    |>Sharma Tester..<LOAD     |<---- Loads previously saved game position
    |                          |
    | [EMPTY].......  SAVE     |<---- Saves current game position
    | [EMPTY].......           |
    | "" ........... FORMAT    |<---- Formats a blank disk for save game
    | "" ...........           |      position
    | "" ...........  PLAY     |<---- Returns back to the play screen
    | "" ...........           |
    | "" ...........           |
    |__________________________|

    Additionally, saved games can be loaded directly from the title screen
    fo faster loading.

    CONTROLS

    Keyboard/Joystick  -  Default  values  Cho can be controlled through a
    compbination of keyboard, keyboard and joystick or by using a joypad.

    KEYBOARD
    UP ARROW - MOVE CHO UP
    DOWN ARROW - MOVE CHO DOWN
    LEFT ARROW - MOVE CHO LEFT
    RIGHT ARROW - MOVE CHO RIGHT

    JOYSTICK
    UP - MOVE CHO UP
    DOWN - MOVE CHO DOWN
    LEFT - MOVE CHO LETF
    RIGHT - MOVE CHO RIGHT
    FIRE BUTTON - FIRE NO.1

    _- - CYCLES BACKWARDS THROUGH OBJECTS COLLECTED

    += - CYCLES FORWARDS THROUGH OBJECTS COLLECTED

    <, - CYCLES BACKWARDS THROUGH WEAPONS COLLECTED

    >. - CYCLES FORWARDS THROUGH WEAPONS COLLECTED

    RIGHT AMIGA KEY - FIRE BUTTON NO.1
    RIGHT ALT KEY   - FIRE BUTTON NO.2
    F2              - Enter INVENTORY MENU
    F5              - Enter LOAD/SAVE MENU

    General

    Joystick/joypad fire buttons substitute for both  fire#1  and  fire#2.
    (If  using  a  one  button  joystick the keyboard must be used for the
    fire#2 function). All the keyboard functions  can  be  redefined  from
    within the options menu.

    2  CD32 CONTROLLER

    TOP LEFT BUTTON - REWIND, Cycle backwards through weapons

    TOP RIGHT BUTTON - FAST FORWARD, Cycle forwards through weapons

    DIRECTION BUTTONS - Pressing in the direction you wish to move will
    allow you to navigate around the play area.

    START BUTTON - PAUSE, This button allows you to enter
                   the SAVE/LOAD MENU

    GREEN - This button allows you to enter the INVENTORY MENU

    RED(Fire#1) - This button allows you to LOOK AT, TALK or USE WEAPONS

    BLUE(Fire#2) - This button allows you to USE, GIVE and PICK UP objects

    YELLOW - Cycles through objects held in inventory. Hold button down
             and press either REWIND or FAST FORWARD

    General

    The green button will enter the inventory screen. It is also  possible
    to  scroll  back and forth through Cho`s weapons without accessing the
    inventory screen by pressing the top flipper  buttons.  Alternatively,
    to  scroll  through  Cho`s  objects, repeat the process whilst holding
    down the yellow button.

    Inventory

    Pressing the F2 key or simultaneously pressing both fire#1 and  fire#2
    enters  Cho`s  inventory screen. Repeating this process will also exit
    from this screen. Cursor  keys,  joystick  or  joypad  will  move  the
    highlighter.  Pressing fire#1 selects the item highlighted for use and
    fire#2 gives a description of the item selected. This applies in  both
    the weapon and objects submenus.

    During  the  game it is possible to shortcut this process. On the game
    screen use the `+` and `-` keys to scroll through all objects and  the
    `<` and `>` keys to scroll through all weapons Cho carries. The object
    and weapon shown are both then ready for use.

    Fight

    Cho uses his chosen weapon by pressing fire#1.

    Examine Object/Pick up Object

    When Cho stands in front of certain objects and eye icon  will  appear
    above his head. You may examine the object by pressing fire#1 and pick
    it up by pressing fire#2.

    Some objects such  as  signposts  cannot  be  picked  up  but  can  be
    examined.

    Talk/Use Object

    When  Cho  is  standing  next  to  any of the inhabitants os Speris, a
    speech icon will appear indicating you are able to have a conversation
    with that character. Vital pieces of information can be gained in this
    manner.

    Fire#1 will start the conversation and you can choose Cho`s repl  from
    the  list.  Other  possible replies are then shown so you can continue
    talking. To finish the conversation select the bottom phrase.

    Fire#2 will attempt to use an object Cho has selected or, if a  speech
    bubble  is  displayed,  Cho will attempt to give the curently selected
    item to the person he`s talking to. Try using  Cho`s  items  on  other
    objects in the game. You never know what might happen..!

    Open Chest

    Stand  in  front of the chest and press fire#1. Cho will automatically
    open the chest and pick up the contents before him.

    Operate Switches

    When Cho stands in front of a switch, pressing fire#1 will trigger it.

